anyone have a recipe for bbq sauce using grape jelly bbq sauce cup ketchup cup grape jelly tablespoon chili powder teaspoon ground black pepper cup finely chopped onion teaspoon lemon juice teaspoon mustard teaspoon worchestershire sauce heat all ingredients in a small sauce pan until the jelly dissolves the sugar in the jelly will burn quickly so don't apply any sauce until your meat is already done this will keep the sauce from burning and ruining your dish i think it goes great with burgers hot dogs smoked sausage pork chops chicken and yes even grilled salmon Hot dog MRE Hamburger Cuisine of Denmark Japanese cuisine Ketchup German cuisine Cajun cuisine Chili con carne Cantonese cuisine D__ner kebab Sauce Haggis Jewish cuisine Curry Korean cuisine Cuisine of Vietnam Mayonnaise Chile pepper Cuisine of Singapore Cuisine of Africa Cuisine of the Southern United States Satay Cuisine of the Philippines Cuisine of Brazil Peruvian cuisine French fries Cuisine of Malaysia Pizza Cincinnati chili Salad Cuisine of Laos Porridge Hot sauce Culinary mustard Meatloaf Cooking weights and measures Worcestershire sauce Nabemono Gumbo Polish cuisine Cuisine of Greece Pancake Kelantan Cuisine of Argentina Cuisine of Cambodia A&W Restaurants Hot pot Ramen Vegetarian cuisine Cha chaan teng Tea Food Turkish coffee Gyros Idli Coffee Street food Roman eating and drinking Cuisine of Austria Wasabi Sichuan Pepper Cuisine of Turkey Dim sum Taiwanese cuisine Jiaozi Breakfast Chicken soup Burger Sunday roast Bacon Canadian Chinese cuisine Recipe Muesli Cuisine of Canada Cheesesteak Halva Souvlaki Caesar salad Capsicum Rice pudding French cuisine In-N-Out Burger Kung pao chicken Dolma Soup Potato pancakes 